# eMudhra intermediate CAs for api.mospi.gov.in.
#
# The server presents two different certificates with the SAME subject
# (CN=EM DV TLS CA - G2A-1): one cross-signed by Comodo 'AAA Certificate
# Services' (a root Mozilla/certifi no longer ship) and one issued by
# 'emSign Root TLS CA - G1'. OpenSSL's path builder takes the first match
# by subject, picks the AAA-signed one, and dead-ends at an untrusted
# self-signed root (verify error 19).
#
# Supplying both eMudhra intermediates as additional trust anchors lets
# the path builder disambiguate; the chain still terminates at
# 'emSign Root CA - G1', which certifi trusts. No verification flags are
# relaxed and no distrusted root is added.
#
# Refresh with:
#   openssl s_client -connect api.mospi.gov.in:443 \
#     -servername api.mospi.gov.in -showcerts

